Titolo: Split Personalities (video game)

Anno: 1986

Descrizione: Split Personalities (first released as Splitting Images) is a sliding square puzzle game that involves piecing together the faces of famous personalities and politicians. The game was developed for the ZX Spectrum by Ernieware and published by Domark, who also ported the game to the Amstrad CPC, Commodore 64 and Commodore Plus/4. The game was later released in 1993 for the Game Boy under the name Splitz.